      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(xai): rediscover retired OAuth token endpoint",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nIssue https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/84018 reports xAI OAuth refresh hitting `https://auth.x.ai/oauth/token` and receiving a Cloudflare CAPTCHA/HTML response. I did not find evidence that `/oauth/token` is a supported xAI endpoint or that OpenClaw source historically hardcoded it for xAI, but OpenClaw refresh does trust a persisted credential `tokenEndpoint` before rediscovering current metadata.\n\nCurrent xAI discovery returns `https://auth.x.ai/oauth2/token`. If a saved credential contains the bad/stale `/oauth/token` endpoint, refresh keeps posting there and receives Cloudflare HTML instead of OAuth JSON.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n`extensions/xai/xai-oauth.ts` already stores the discovered endpoint for new OAuth and device-code credentials. This change only special-cases the known unsupported xAI `/oauth/token` endpoint during refresh: if a credential has `/oauth/token`, OpenClaw rediscovers the current token endpoint before posting, and the successful refresh writes the canonical `/oauth2/token` endpoint back into the credential.\n\nMinimal live repro with fake tokens, current endpoint:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sS -o /dev/null -X POST \"https://auth.x.ai/oauth2/token\" -H \"Accept: application/json\" -H \"Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" --data \"grant_type=refresh_token&client_id=b1a00492-073a-47ea-816f-4c329264a828&refresh_token=not-a-real-refresh-token\" -w \"http_code=%{http_code} content_type=%{content_type}\\n\"\n```\n\nMinimal live repro with fake tokens, reported unsupported endpoint:\n\n```bash\ncurl -sS -o /dev/null -X POST \"https://auth.x.ai/oauth/token\" -H \"Accept: application/json\" -H \"Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" --data \"grant_type=refresh_token&client_id=b1a00492-073a-47ea-816f-4c329264a828&refresh_token=not-a-real-refresh-token\" -w \"http_code=%{http_code} content_type=%{content_type}\\n\"\n```\n\nObserved live result while preparing this PR:\n\n```text\nhttps://auth.x.ai/oauth2/token -> 400 application/json, OAuth error invalid_grant\nhttps://auth.x.ai/oauth/token  -> 403 text/html; charset=UTF-8, server cloudflare\n```\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers with stale or bad persisted xAI OAuth credentials no longer get stuck on the unsupported Cloudflare-served endpoint. Their next refresh attempts the current endpoint from xAI discovery and normalizes the stored endpoint after a successful refresh.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `pnpm test extensions/xai/xai-oauth.test.ts`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm check`\n- Full `pnpm test` was attempted and failed in unrelated broad-suite areas after this PR's targeted test, build, and check passed.\n- Live dummy POST probes above confirmed `/oauth2/token` returns OAuth JSON while `/oauth/token` returns Cloudflare HTML.",
        "branch": "fix/xai-oauth-stale-token-endpoint",
        "head_sha": "ede4d61d0174a1c1577ec125acce6578a717e11a",
